# AI Backend Engineering

- Read `ai-backend-src/docs/README.md`, the relevant PRD, and the matching spec before implementation.
- `ai-backend-src` is transitional; future canonical service path is `services/ai-backend`.
- Keep orchestration separate from connector side effects.
- Use dependency inversion for registries, stores, MCP clients, and subagent runners.
- Do not expose unauthorized tools, MCP servers, memories, or skills to the model.
- Do not put product persistence, tenant auth ownership, or app-specific presentation logic in the AI backend.
- Update docs when implementation changes a contract, invariant, or edge case.

